Preheat your oven to 200°C and put a large #saucepan{} of water with a @salt{pinch} on to boil for the rice. Pop the @British chicken breasts{2} into a #mixing bowl{} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Sprinkle on half of the @Mexican style spice mix{1}. Shake the tin of @coconut milk{200%ml} to break up the solids, then pour one-third over the chicken. Mix to make sure that the chicken is well coated. Keep to one side.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands after handling raw meat.

When the water is boiling, add half the @chicken stock powder{1/2}, a good pinch of @salt{} and the @brown basmati rice{150%g} to the pan. Cook until tender, ~{25-30%minutes}. Add more water to the pan if it is absorbed by the rice.

Whilst the rice cooks, separate the @broccoli{1} into florets (mini trees). Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). Roughly chop the @coriander{10%g}(roughly chopped) (stalks and all). Zest and juice the @lime{1}.

Heat a #frying pan{} over high heat and add splash of @oil{}. Carefully add the chicken and cook until nicely browned, ~{2-3%minutes} on each side. Transfer to a lined #baking tray{} (don't wash your pan we'll use it again) and roast on the top shelf of your oven for ~{15-17%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when it is no longer pink in the middle. Discard the excess marinade.

When your chicken has 10 mins left, add the broccoli to the baking tray with the chicken. Roast until golden and crispy.

Once the rice is ready, drain in a #sieve{}, then return to the pan. Cover with a #lid{} to keep warm. It's time to make the sauce. Add the @water{50%ml}, remaining @chicken stock powder{1/2}, @coconut milk{} and remaining Mexican spice mix to the frying pan you used earlier, on medium-high. Bring to the boil, dissolve the stock pot then reduce the heat and gently bubble for ~{2-3%minutes}.

Finish the sauce with lime juice and zest to taste, then stir through the coriander. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if it needs it.

When the chicken is cooked, cut each breast into five slices. Serve on top of a generous portion of rice and finish with the roasted broccoli and the coconut sauce spooned over the chicken. Enjoy!